modules.description: Handles writing batches of numerical data to NPZ files. Supports creating a writer, appending multi-dimensional arrays in C layout, and closing the writer to finalize the file. Useful for saving large datasets incrementally without loading everything into memory at once.

This module reads and writes NumPy `.npz` archive files, handling compressed arrays stored under string keys. It supports loading arrays into preallocated bigarrays or extracting entry names from archives. Typical uses include saving and restoring machine learning model weights or numerical datasets to disk efficiently.
